[While the report on the IHR emergency committee is lengthy, it is an excellent review of the current situation internationally and a solid risk assessment of potential international spread of the polioviruses, both wild polioviruses (WPVs) as well as the circulating vaccine derived polioviruses (cVDPVs).

International spread of the cVDPVs has occurred between Somalia and Kenya in recent years, so concern is there. The other notable discussion is the impact of having an outbreak in countries that have been polio free for some time and now are experiencing cVDPV, such as Papua New Guinea this year (2018), and Syria last year (2017).

Many of these challenges have been raised in prior ProMED-mail posts, but it is a good reminder of the challenges moving forward to the ultimate goal of polio eradication. - Mod.MPP]
